When retrieving a deal by UniqueID with the wrong data type (e.g., boolean), the system still validates it as a string and returns a 404 Not Found error code.

*Steps:*

# Send GET request to url: https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/deal/:UniqueID
# Set UniqueID value to boolean (true or false)

*Expected result:*

(/) The API should return a client error response, such as: HTTP Status Code 400 (Bad Request)

*Example of a Possible Error Response:* 

{noformat}{
    "error": {
        "code": 400,
        "message": "Invalid data type for 'UniqueID': expected string, received boolean."
    }
}{noformat}

*Actual result:*

(x)  The validation with incorrect data type returns 404 Not Found error code.

!deals unique id boolean.jpg|width=1126,height=589,alt="deals unique id boolean.jpg"!

