When sending a GET request with a negative cursor key value (e.g., -10), we get a 500 Internal Server Error. 

*Steps:*

# Send GET request to url: https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/deal?limit=10&cursor=-10

*Expected result:*

(/)  Instead of generating a server error, the API should return a client error response, such as: HTTP Status Code 400 (Bad Request) - {{"Cursor value must be a non-negative integer."}} (example)

*Actual result:*

(x)  The negative cursor value leads to a 500 Internal Server Error.

